Creating files with Artisan

Instead of creating files manually, you can use Artisan commands:

# Create a model
php artisan make:model Product

# Create a controller
php artisan make:controller ProductController

# Create a model, migration, controller, factory, and seeder
php artisan make:model Product -mcrfs

The generated files will be placed in the appropriate directories:

Model: app/Models/Product.php
Controller: app/Http/Controllers/ProductController.php
Views: Create them manually under resources/views/ (for example, resources/views/products/index.blade.php).




